1
00:00:03,144 --> 00:00:04,978
-ONCE UPON A TIME,

2
00:00:04,978 --> 00:00:07,878
THERE WAS A PRINCESS
WHO WAS HELD CAPTIVE.

3
00:00:07,878 --> 00:00:10,978
SHE WAS IMPRISONED
IN THE DEMON KING'S CASTLE,

4
00:00:10,978 --> 00:00:13,511
HER FREEDOM TAKEN FROM HER.

5
00:00:13,511 --> 00:00:16,911
THE PRINCESS HAD NO CHOICE
BUT TO DANCE LIKE A PUPPET

6
00:00:16,911 --> 00:00:21,711
TO THE TUNE SET BY THE WHIMS
OF HER SADISTIC CAPTOR.

7
00:00:21,711 --> 00:00:24,944
ONE DAY, A HERO
CAME TO FIGHT THE DEMON KING,

8
00:00:24,944 --> 00:00:27,411
SEEKING TO SAVE THE PRINCESS.

9
00:00:27,411 --> 00:00:31,511
HOWEVER, THERE WAS NO WAY THE
HERO COULD ATTAIN THE VICTORY.

10
00:00:31,511 --> 00:00:32,978
FOR YOU SEE,

11
00:00:32,978 --> 00:00:36,444
THE HERO DID NOT KNOW
THAT HE HIMSELF WAS A PUPPET

12
00:00:36,444 --> 00:00:39,384
THAT THE DEMON KING HAD CREATED.

13
00:00:42,351 --> 00:00:44,818
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

14
00:00:57,051 --> 00:01:00,184
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

15
00:01:25,118 --> 00:01:27,518
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

16
00:02:10,491 --> 00:02:13,558
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S
"FINAL WALTZ AND APOTHEOSIS"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

17
00:02:30,029 --> 00:02:34,196
-[ GASPS ] FAKIR!

18
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:36,996
-[ GASPS ] TUTU!

19
00:02:38,487 --> 00:02:40,587
-WHERE AM I?

20
00:02:40,587 --> 00:02:42,154
GEARS?

21
00:02:42,154 --> 00:02:44,560
WHY ARE THEY ALL STOPPED?

22
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:48,227
WHAT AM I DOING IN A PLACE
LIKE THIS?

23
00:02:48,227 --> 00:02:49,827
WHAT SHOULD I DO NOW?

24
00:02:49,827 --> 00:02:52,027
FAKIR!

25
00:02:54,327 --> 00:02:55,994
-[ GRUNTS ]

26
00:02:55,994 --> 00:02:58,027
[ Thinking ] DROSSELMEYER --

27
00:02:58,027 --> 00:03:00,794
THE MAN WHO TOYS
WITH EVERYONE'S FATES.

28
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,927
IS HE OUT THERE SOMEWHERE,

29
00:03:04,927 --> 00:03:07,827
LAUGHING AS HE WATCHES HER
AND MYTHO SUFFER?

30
00:03:07,827 --> 00:03:10,860
WHERE IS SHE RIGHT NOW?

31
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:13,627
IS SHE WHERE DROSSELMEYER IS?

32
00:03:13,627 --> 00:03:16,627
WHERE THE HELL IS THAT?

33
00:03:16,627 --> 00:03:18,860
-BY NOW, THE STORY
MAY HAVE PROGRESSED

34
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:20,594
TO THE POINT
WHERE WE CAN DO NOTHING.

35
00:03:20,594 --> 00:03:22,527
IN THAT CASE,
THE ONLY ONE WHO CAN FIGHT

36
00:03:22,527 --> 00:03:24,127
IS HE WHO CARRIES
THE SAME BLOOD.

37
00:03:24,127 --> 00:03:26,560
-YOU MEAN I SHOULD WRITE, THEN?

38
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:27,960
THERE'S NO OTHER WAY
THAT I'LL BE ABLE

39
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,827
TO SAVE HER AT THIS POINT.

40
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,860
-WHERE IS THE EXIT?

41
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:38,127
I MUST LEAVE THIS PLACE.

42
00:03:38,127 --> 00:03:39,860
I KNOW WHERE THEY ARE.

43
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:44,567
THE OTHER HEART SHARDS ARE IN
THE FIVE GATES AROUND THE TOWN.

44
00:03:44,567 --> 00:03:47,300
I MUST RETURN THEM
TO MYTHO SOON.

45
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:51,667
AND THEN MYTHO WILL RETURN
TO THE STORY,

46
00:03:51,667 --> 00:03:55,600
AND I'LL GO BACK
TO BEING...A DUCK.

47
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,834
[ WHIZ! ]

48
00:03:56,834 --> 00:03:58,034
[ CLATTER! ]
WHAT'S THIS?

49
00:03:58,034 --> 00:03:59,834
A PUPPET?

50
00:03:59,834 --> 00:04:03,034
-YES! THAT'S RIGHT!
YOU'RE IN THE PUPPET WORLD NOW!

51
00:04:03,034 --> 00:04:04,734
[ LAUGHS ]
-WHO'S THIS?

52
00:04:04,734 --> 00:04:07,067
YOU'RE PRINCESS TUTU,
AREN'T YOU?

53
00:04:07,067 --> 00:04:09,100
-[ CHUCKLES ] IT'S TUTU!

54
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,834
IT'S TUTU!
IT'S PRINCESS TUTU!

55
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:13,734
-I WONDER WHAT TUTU IS
DOING HERE?!

56
00:04:13,734 --> 00:04:15,700
-DO YOU KNOW
WHERE THIS PLACE IS?

57
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,334
PLEASE TELL ME!

58
00:04:17,334 --> 00:04:19,667
WHY WAS I BROUGHT HERE?
WAS THERE SOME REASON?

59
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:22,800
WHY HAS EVERYTHING IN THIS PLACE
JUST STOPPED?

60
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,267
-THAT'S RATHER IRRESPONSIBLE
OF YOU, WOULDN'T YOU SAY --

61
00:04:25,267 --> 00:04:26,567
NOT KNOWING WHERE YOU ARE?

62
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:28,534
-THEN PLEASE! TELL ME!

63
00:04:28,534 --> 00:04:31,034
-TUTU SAYS SHE WANTS US
TO TELL HER.

64
00:04:31,034 --> 00:04:32,600
-PRINCESS TUTU IN A PICKLE!

65
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,700
-A PICKLE!

66
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:37,100
[ LAUGHTER ]

67
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:38,500
-ANSWER ME!

68
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,034
[ LAUGHTER STOPS ]

69
00:04:40,034 --> 00:04:43,007
-YOU'RE THE ONE WHO STOPPED
EVERYTHING, PRINCESS TUTU.

70
00:04:43,007 --> 00:04:44,207
DIDN'T YOU KNOW?

71
00:04:44,207 --> 00:04:46,007
-THIS IS THE INSIDE
OF THE STORY.

72
00:04:46,007 --> 00:04:48,640
-AND YOU ARE THE ONE
WHO CAUSED THE STORY TO STOP.

73
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:50,807
-CAUSED THE STORY TO STOP?

74
00:04:50,807 --> 00:04:52,840
I DID IT?
-THAT'S RIGHT!

75
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,640
TUTU STOPPED THE STORY!

76
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:56,740
-TUTU STOPPED ALL THE GEARS!

77
00:04:56,740 --> 00:04:58,974
SHE STOPPED THEM!
SHE STOPPED THEM!

78
00:04:58,974 --> 00:05:02,907
TUTU STOPPED THEM!
TUTU STOPPED THEM!

79
00:05:02,907 --> 00:05:05,274
-STOP IT!

80
00:05:05,274 --> 00:05:06,740
[ GASPS ]

81
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,340
MY BODY!

82
00:05:08,340 --> 00:05:10,374
IT WON'T MOVE!

83
00:05:21,007 --> 00:05:23,407
-[ Thinking ] HEAR THE VOICE
WHICH IS VOICELESS

84
00:05:23,407 --> 00:05:25,574
AND SEE THE SHAPE
WHICH IS SHAPELESS.

85
00:05:25,574 --> 00:05:28,207
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO WITH THAT?

86
00:05:28,207 --> 00:05:30,640
WHAT SHOULD I WRITE?

87
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:34,874
[ STRAINING ]

88
00:05:34,874 --> 00:05:36,140
[ GRUNTS ]

89
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:42,647
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

90
00:05:46,114 --> 00:05:47,480
DAMN IT!

91
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:49,414
I HAVE TO WRITE!

92
00:05:52,247 --> 00:05:55,247
I HAVE TO WRITE.

93
00:05:55,247 --> 00:05:58,114
[ PANTING ]

94
00:05:58,114 --> 00:06:00,680
-[ GROANS ]

95
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,980
WHERE IS THE HEART?

96
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:06,880
DAUGHTER, HURRY UP AND FETCH ME
A HEART.

97
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,047
-DEAR FATHER,
NOW THAT I HAVE GONE

98
00:06:10,047 --> 00:06:12,214
AND DYED THE PRINCE'S HEART
IN YOUR BLOOD,

99
00:06:12,214 --> 00:06:14,780
HE'LL DEFINITELY BECOME
MINE, RIGHT, FATHER?

100
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:20,047
-ARE YOU SAYING YOU CANNOT TRUST
WHAT I TELL YOU?

101
00:06:20,047 --> 00:06:22,447
-OH, NO! OF COURSE NOT!

102
00:06:22,447 --> 00:06:24,180
-AND TO THINK ON TOP OF THAT,

103
00:06:24,180 --> 00:06:28,114
YOU ONLY CONSIDER YOURSELF
AND NOT ME, YOUR FATHER.

104
00:06:28,114 --> 00:06:31,014
-THAT'S NOT TRUE!
I LOVE YOU, FATHER, BUT --

105
00:06:31,014 --> 00:06:34,447
-IT'S ONLY NATURAL FOR
A DAUGHTER TO LOVE HER FATHER!

106
00:06:34,447 --> 00:06:37,914
[ RUMBLE! ]
YOU'RE PATHETIC.

107
00:06:37,914 --> 00:06:39,614
TO THINK YOU CAN'T EVEN

108
00:06:39,614 --> 00:06:41,280
GET THE LOVE OF THE PRINCE
IN THE STORY.

109
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:43,087
AT THIS POINT,

110
00:06:43,087 --> 00:06:45,654
YOU NO LONGER HAVE ANY VALUE
TO ME AS A DAUGHTER.

111
00:06:45,654 --> 00:06:47,020
-[ GASPS ] FATHER!

112
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:49,854
-YOU SHOULD AT LEAST
GIVE ME YOUR HEART

113
00:06:49,854 --> 00:06:53,287
SO THAT I MIGHT BE RESTORED
TO SOME DEGREE, HOWEVER SMALL.

114
00:06:53,287 --> 00:06:54,820
-FATHER! [ WHIMPERS ]

115
00:06:54,820 --> 00:06:56,920
FORGIVE ME! I'M SORRY!

116
00:06:56,920 --> 00:07:01,220
-I HAVE NOT GIVEN YOU LEAVE,
KRAEHE!

117
00:07:01,220 --> 00:07:05,887
-HAVE I...TURNED INTO A PUPPET?

118
00:07:05,887 --> 00:07:08,787
DID I DO SOMETHING BAD,
IS THAT WHY?

119
00:07:08,787 --> 00:07:11,220
[ TAPPING ]
[ GASPS ]

120
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:13,587
IS THAT...?

121
00:07:13,587 --> 00:07:14,754
UZURA!

122
00:07:14,754 --> 00:07:16,087
-OH!

123
00:07:16,087 --> 00:07:18,654
I FOUND TUTU, ZURA!

124
00:07:18,654 --> 00:07:20,620
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE, UZURA?

125
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:23,454
-I FOLLOWED YOU, ZURA!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING, ZURA?

126
00:07:23,454 --> 00:07:26,754
-I THINK I'VE SOMEHOW
TURNED INTO A PUPPET.

127
00:07:26,754 --> 00:07:29,120
-A PUPPET, ZURA?

128
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:32,287
-UH, IT'S NOT THAT
I DON'T LIKE BEING A PUPPET.

129
00:07:32,287 --> 00:07:34,454
IT'S JUST --
-OOH!

130
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:35,787
-UZURA?

131
00:07:35,787 --> 00:07:38,687
-OOH, OOH.

132
00:07:42,827 --> 00:07:44,160
PUPPETS, ZURA?

133
00:07:46,594 --> 00:07:48,860
[ SCREAMS ]
-UZURA!

134
00:07:48,860 --> 00:07:52,127
-JETé ENTRELACé.

135
00:07:52,127 --> 00:07:54,360
-[ GASPS ]

136
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,660
MY FEET ARE MOVING ON THEIR OWN!

137
00:07:56,660 --> 00:07:59,694
-FOUETTé ROND DE JAMBE
EN TOURNANT.

138
00:07:59,694 --> 00:08:02,060
-MR. DROSSELMEYER?

139
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:05,627
IS THIS THE WORLD
WHERE MR. DROSSELMEYER IS?

140
00:08:05,627 --> 00:08:09,127
HOW? WHY?

141
00:08:09,127 --> 00:08:14,394
I'M JUST A MARIONETTE
DANCING EXACTLY AS I'M TOLD.

142
00:08:14,394 --> 00:08:16,660
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

143
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:20,160
I WANT TO DANCE MORE --
MORE FREELY!

144
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:22,694
-SUCH THINKING IS MISTAKEN.

145
00:08:22,694 --> 00:08:25,094
MARIONETTES ARE
AT THEIR MOST FREE

146
00:08:25,094 --> 00:08:28,594
WHEN THEY'RE BEING MANIPULATED
BY THEIR STRINGS.

147
00:08:28,594 --> 00:08:31,027
YOU WON'T BE ABLE
TO LEAVE THIS PLACE

148
00:08:31,027 --> 00:08:33,060
UNLESS YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT.

149
00:08:33,060 --> 00:08:33,994
[ LAUGHS ]

150
00:08:33,994 --> 00:08:35,527
-WHAT'S A PUPPET, ZURA?

151
00:08:35,527 --> 00:08:37,660
-WELL, HER NAME IS UZURA.

152
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:40,760
BUT KARON -- HE MADE HER
FROM THE WOOD FROM EDEL

153
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,234
THAT DIDN'T BURN UP.

154
00:08:42,234 --> 00:08:43,534
-FROM MISS EDEL?

155
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,334
-DOES THAT MEAN
I'M NOT UZURA, ZURA?

156
00:08:48,334 --> 00:08:49,834
HUH?

157
00:08:49,834 --> 00:08:51,167
OH!

158
00:08:51,167 --> 00:08:53,434
[ FOOTSTEPS ]

159
00:08:53,434 --> 00:08:54,867
[ GASPS ]

160
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,500
WHAT'S THIS, ZURA?

161
00:08:56,500 --> 00:09:00,000
[ CLANKING ]
OH, IT TURNS, ZURA!

162
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,800
[ CLANKS ]

163
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:05,434
OOH!

164
00:09:05,434 --> 00:09:07,800
[ BIRD CAWING ]

165
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,200
-CAW CAW. [ LAUGHS ]

166
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,034
[ DOOR OPENS ]

167
00:09:12,034 --> 00:09:14,400
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

168
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,667
HELLO, KRAEHE.

169
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:17,400
COME HERE, WON'T YOU?

170
00:09:17,400 --> 00:09:20,100
[ LAUGHS ]
-[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

171
00:09:20,100 --> 00:09:22,400
-MY PRINCE --
-COME, COME, NOW.

172
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:24,300
WHY THE HAUNTED LOOK?

173
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:26,300
LET'S ENJOY OURSELVES.

174
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:28,334
I WANT TO GET
THE ALL MY FEELINGS BACK --

175
00:09:28,334 --> 00:09:30,100
THE SOONER, THE BETTER.

176
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:33,734
ONCE THAT'S TAKEN CARE OF,
I CAN GIVE THE RAVEN MY HEART.

177
00:09:33,734 --> 00:09:35,567
-[ GASPS ]
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

178
00:09:35,567 --> 00:09:36,967
THAT'S A JOKE, RIGHT?

179
00:09:36,967 --> 00:09:39,434
THE PRINCE IS FATED
TO MARRY NO ONE BUT ME.

180
00:09:39,434 --> 00:09:41,300
-MARRY YOU?

181
00:09:41,300 --> 00:09:43,407
YOU, WHO IN SPITE
OF BEING A CROW,

182
00:09:43,407 --> 00:09:45,740
HAVE THAT UGLY HUMAN BODY?

183
00:09:45,740 --> 00:09:47,707
THAT'S THE JOKE.

184
00:09:47,707 --> 00:09:50,540
THE ONLY THING THAT YOU
ARE ALLOWED TO DO IS LOVE ME.

185
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:51,907
-[ GASPS ]

186
00:09:51,907 --> 00:09:54,974
-THE MOMENT YOU DYED MY HEART
WITH RAVEN'S BLOOD,

187
00:09:54,974 --> 00:09:58,174
OUR FATES
WERE IMMEDIATELY SEALED.

188
00:09:58,174 --> 00:10:01,107
-[ Thinking ] BUT I DID JUST
WHAT FATHER TOLD ME TO.

189
00:10:01,107 --> 00:10:04,907
THEN I -- THEN I'D RATHER JUST
TAKE HIS HEART OUT AGAIN.

190
00:10:04,907 --> 00:10:08,307
BUT I DON'T HAVE
THE PRINCE'S SWORD.

191
00:10:08,307 --> 00:10:12,674
IF I THRUST THIS SWORD
INTO THE PRINCE, HE MIGHT DIE.

192
00:10:12,674 --> 00:10:14,174
THAT'S FINE.

193
00:10:14,174 --> 00:10:16,307
IF THAT HAPPENS, I, TOO, WILL --

194
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,040
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

195
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:23,507
-I HAVE ONE LAST FAVOR TO ASK --

196
00:10:23,507 --> 00:10:26,107
AFTER YOU'VE RIPPED OUT
MY HEART,

197
00:10:26,107 --> 00:10:27,674
I WANT YOU TO KISS IT

198
00:10:27,674 --> 00:10:29,974
AND DYE YOUR LIPS CRIMSON
WITH MY BLOOD.

199
00:10:29,974 --> 00:10:31,940
-[ GASPS ]

200
00:10:34,174 --> 00:10:35,574
-WHAT'S THE MATTER?

201
00:10:35,574 --> 00:10:37,307
CAN'T YOU DO IT?

202
00:10:37,307 --> 00:10:38,774
[ LAUGHS ]

203
00:10:38,774 --> 00:10:43,280
-WELL, LOOKS LIKE YOU'VE REACHED
YOUR LIMIT.

204
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:46,647
I'LL ADMIT, PICKING
DROSSELMEYER'S GRAVE TO WRITE AT

205
00:10:46,647 --> 00:10:48,914
WAS PRETTY SHARP -- FOR YOU.

206
00:10:48,914 --> 00:10:50,880
BUT IF THE WORDS
YOU SHOULD BE WRITING

207
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:53,247
AREN'T COMING TO YOU WITHOUT
YOU EVEN HAVING TO THINK --

208
00:10:53,247 --> 00:10:55,514
-COULD YOU PLEASE BE
A LITTLE QUIETER?

209
00:10:55,514 --> 00:10:57,280
-AND TO THINK, AT THIS MOMENT,

210
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:59,614
I HAVE VOLUMES UPON VOLUMES
THAT I WANT TO WRITE.

211
00:10:59,614 --> 00:11:00,914
IT'S IRONIC.

212
00:11:00,914 --> 00:11:02,714
-FASTER!

213
00:11:02,714 --> 00:11:04,414
I'VE GOT TO WRITE FASTER!

214
00:11:04,414 --> 00:11:05,580
-GOOD GRIEF!

215
00:11:05,580 --> 00:11:07,747
YOU'D BE BETTER OFF
LETTING THE STORY

216
00:11:07,747 --> 00:11:10,180
PULL YOU ALONG LIKE A GOOD BOY.

217
00:11:10,180 --> 00:11:12,747
WELL,
IT'S OF NO REAL CONSEQUENCE.

218
00:11:12,747 --> 00:11:14,780
YOU NEEDN'T FRET, LITTLE DUCK.

219
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:18,247
I'LL BE COMING FOR YOU SOON.

220
00:11:18,247 --> 00:11:23,214
[ TCHAIKOVSKY'S "MARCH"
FROM "THE NUTCRACKER" PLAYS ]

221
00:11:28,247 --> 00:11:30,747
[ BIRD CAWING ]

222
00:11:30,747 --> 00:11:33,247
[ RUSTLING ]

223
00:11:33,247 --> 00:11:34,847
-[ LAUGHING ]

224
00:11:34,847 --> 00:11:36,180
[ GRUNTS ]

225
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,047
[ ALL CAWING ]

226
00:11:38,047 --> 00:11:40,880
[ GIGGLING ]

227
00:11:46,887 --> 00:11:48,254
-[ GASPS ]

228
00:11:48,254 --> 00:11:50,687
[ DRINK POURING ]
WHO'S THERE?

229
00:11:50,687 --> 00:11:54,254
-WELCOME TO THIS QUAINT,
LITTLE GAP IN TIME,

230
00:11:54,254 --> 00:11:56,420
MY DEAR PRINCESS TUTU.

231
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:58,287
-MR. DROSSELMEYER!

232
00:11:58,287 --> 00:12:00,720
SO, WHAT DID THOSE PUPPETS MEAN

233
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,887
WHEN THEY TOLD ME
I STOPPED THE STORY?

234
00:12:02,887 --> 00:12:05,787
I'M JUST...[Straining]

235
00:12:05,787 --> 00:12:07,154
...TRYING MY BEST

236
00:12:07,154 --> 00:12:09,120
TO COMPLETELY RETURN
THE PRINCE'S HEART TO HIM.

237
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:10,687
-TELL ME, HAVE YOU DISCOVERED

238
00:12:10,687 --> 00:12:13,420
ALL THE LOCATIONS
OF THE SCATTERED HEART SHARDS?

239
00:12:13,420 --> 00:12:15,720
-WHAT? UM, I'M NOT QUITE SURE,

240
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,987
BUT I THINK THAT THEY'RE HIDDEN
IN THE FIVE GATES AROUND THE T--

241
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:21,054
-MY CONGRATULATIONS TO YOU.
-WHAT?

242
00:12:21,054 --> 00:12:23,487
SO, IF I RETURN THOSE
FIVE SHARDS TO HIM,

243
00:12:23,487 --> 00:12:25,587
THE PRINCE WILL GO BACK
TO NORMAL AND DEFEAT THE RAVEN

244
00:12:25,587 --> 00:12:27,287
AND THEN --
-NO, NO, NO.

245
00:12:27,287 --> 00:12:29,454
THAT WOULD BE HOPELESSLY BORING!

246
00:12:29,454 --> 00:12:31,120
YOU'RE A STORY CHARACTER.

247
00:12:31,120 --> 00:12:32,620
YOU CAN DO BETTER THAN THAT!

248
00:12:32,620 --> 00:12:34,587
-CHARACTER?

249
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:35,620
BUT HOW CAN THAT BE?

250
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:37,220
I'M REALLY ONLY A DUCK.

251
00:12:37,220 --> 00:12:40,654
-CORRECT, BUT YOU'RE
INSIDE THE STORY RIGHT NOW.

252
00:12:40,654 --> 00:12:42,087
EVERYBODY IS.

253
00:12:42,087 --> 00:12:44,327
TAKE A LOOK.
-[ GASPS ] HUH?

254
00:12:44,327 --> 00:12:46,194
[ CLANK! ]

255
00:12:46,194 --> 00:12:48,027
RUE.

256
00:12:48,027 --> 00:12:49,760
FAKIR.

257
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:51,494
MYTHO!

258
00:12:51,494 --> 00:12:53,827
-EVERYONE'S SUFFERING, YOU SEE.

259
00:12:53,827 --> 00:12:55,827
THIS IS THE WAY IT HAS TO BE.

260
00:12:55,827 --> 00:12:58,927
TUTU HAS SOMETHING
SHE SHOULD SUFFER OVER, TOO --

261
00:12:58,927 --> 00:13:02,427
THE CHOICE TO CONFESS HER LOVE
AND IMMEDIATELY VANISH,

262
00:13:02,427 --> 00:13:04,294
OR NEVER TO CONFESS HER LOVE

263
00:13:04,294 --> 00:13:06,860
AND, THEREBY,
FOREVER LOSE THE PRINCE.

264
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:08,194
-NEVER MIND THAT. I --

265
00:13:08,194 --> 00:13:11,027
-AND YET, TO THINK
RETURNING THE PRINCE TO NORMAL

266
00:13:11,027 --> 00:13:13,927
IS MORE IMPORTANT TO YOU
THAN YOUR OWN PROBLEMS.

267
00:13:15,327 --> 00:13:18,860
YOU'RE A MUCH DIFFERENT DUCK NOW
THAN THE ONE YOU ONCE WERE,

268
00:13:18,860 --> 00:13:21,660
WHOSE SOLE DESIRE
WAS FOR THE PRINCE!

269
00:13:21,660 --> 00:13:24,160
YOU SHOULD BE DESPERATELY
IN LOVE WITH THE PRINCE

270
00:13:24,160 --> 00:13:25,260
AND WANT TO MARRY HIM!

271
00:13:25,260 --> 00:13:26,560
AM I WRONG?

272
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:28,027
-I JUST...

273
00:13:28,027 --> 00:13:29,460
-THAT'S RIGHT!

274
00:13:29,460 --> 00:13:31,994
YOU SHOULDN'T FIGHT
WHAT'S NATURAL.

275
00:13:31,994 --> 00:13:34,727
IT'S ONLY NATURAL TO WANT
TO MAKE THE PRINCE YOURS,

276
00:13:34,727 --> 00:13:36,294
AND YOURS ALONE.

277
00:13:36,294 --> 00:13:39,260
THERE'S NOTHING
TO BE ASHAMED OF.

278
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:40,460
I KNOW.

279
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:42,367
HOW DOES THIS IDEA
APPEAL TO YOUR NATURE?

280
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:44,533
SIMPLY PRETEND
YOU HAVEN'T REALIZED

281
00:13:44,533 --> 00:13:47,500
THAT THE REMAINING HEART SHARDS
ARE HIDDEN IN THE FIVE GATES.

282
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,300
-WHAT?
-AFTER ALL,

283
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:51,400
NOBODY ELSE HAS REALIZED,

284
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,033
SO IF YOU DO THAT,

285
00:13:53,033 --> 00:13:55,767
THERE WILL BE NOTHING
TO PART YOU FROM THE PRINCE.

286
00:13:55,767 --> 00:13:57,367
-BUT --
-MY DEAR DUCK,

287
00:13:57,367 --> 00:13:59,700
IF YOU CAN'T THINK
AT LEAST ON THAT LEVEL,

288
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:00,867
YOU'LL NEVER LEAVE HERE,

289
00:14:00,867 --> 00:14:03,400
AND THE STORY
WILL STAY STOPPED, TOO.

290
00:14:03,400 --> 00:14:05,000
[ GASPS ]
-[ GASPS ]

291
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:07,167
-WHAT'S THIS?

292
00:14:07,167 --> 00:14:09,967
TUTU IS HERE,
AND YET THE GEARS ARE MOVING?

293
00:14:09,967 --> 00:14:11,367
WHAT IS GOING ON?

294
00:14:11,367 --> 00:14:13,700
OOH.

295
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,467
INTERESTING!

296
00:14:15,467 --> 00:14:18,200
THE GEARS ARE STARTING
TO TURN BACKWARDS.

297
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,734
THE STORY WILL NOW
DOUBLE BACK ON ITSELF!

298
00:14:20,734 --> 00:14:23,100
-WHAT?
-WHOA! WHOA!

299
00:14:23,100 --> 00:14:25,600
-I NEVER ONCE
ENVISIONED SOMETHING LIKE THIS!

300
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:27,100
HOW INTRIGUING!

301
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:29,467
I WONDER WHAT WILL HAPPEN.

302
00:14:29,467 --> 00:14:32,067
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

303
00:14:32,067 --> 00:14:35,034
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND ANYMORE.

304
00:14:35,034 --> 00:14:37,000
I BELIEVED THAT MY MARRIAGE
TO THE PRINCE

305
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,467
WAS THE FATE
THE STORY HAD DECIDED FOR US.

306
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:41,974
WAS I WRONG?

307
00:14:41,974 --> 00:14:43,040
WHAT SHOULD I BELIEVE?

308
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:44,740
WHOM SHOULD I BELIEVE?

309
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:47,240
[ SOBBING ]

310
00:14:48,674 --> 00:14:52,740
I WANT TO GO BACK TO THAT TIME
BEFORE I REMEMBERED EVERYTHING,

311
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:54,507
THAT TIME WHEN I WAS RUE!

312
00:14:56,507 --> 00:14:58,507
[ BELL TOLLING ]

313
00:15:00,907 --> 00:15:03,374
-HELP ME!

314
00:15:03,374 --> 00:15:05,974
[ TOLLING CONTINUES ]

315
00:15:05,974 --> 00:15:09,040
[ CRYING ]

316
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,574
I'M SORRY, FATHER!

317
00:15:10,574 --> 00:15:14,007
DON'T TAKE MY HEART! FORGIVE ME!

318
00:15:14,007 --> 00:15:16,540
[ CRYING ]

319
00:15:16,540 --> 00:15:18,474
-THAT WAS...

320
00:15:18,474 --> 00:15:20,474
-I'LL BE A GOOD GIRL!

321
00:15:20,474 --> 00:15:22,507
-[ GASPS ]

322
00:15:22,507 --> 00:15:23,774
-[ GRUNTS ]

323
00:15:26,107 --> 00:15:27,607
-GET BEHIND ME.

324
00:15:27,607 --> 00:15:29,007
-[ WHIMPERS ]

325
00:15:29,007 --> 00:15:31,507
[ BIRD CAWING ]

326
00:15:45,480 --> 00:15:48,580
-THAT'S THE PRINCE
BACK WHEN I FIRST MET HIM.

327
00:15:52,514 --> 00:15:54,814
-YOU DON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ANYMORE.

328
00:16:03,547 --> 00:16:06,280
[ GROANS ]

329
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,780
-D-DOES IT HURT?

330
00:16:08,780 --> 00:16:10,780
-[ LIGHTLY GROANING ]

331
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:17,614
-I-I BROUGHT WATER.

332
00:16:17,614 --> 00:16:18,880
-[ LIGHTLY GROANS ]

333
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:21,847
-[ GASPS ]

334
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:29,047
-THANK YOU.

335
00:16:29,047 --> 00:16:31,747
-I HAVE TO GO.
-GO WHERE?

336
00:16:31,747 --> 00:16:33,780
-BACK HOME TO MY FATHER.

337
00:16:33,780 --> 00:16:34,947
-WHO ARE YOU?

338
00:16:34,947 --> 00:16:37,014
-MY NAME IS...

339
00:16:37,014 --> 00:16:40,747
-MY PITIFUL DAUGHTER,
WHO DESPITE BEING A CROW,

340
00:16:40,747 --> 00:16:43,654
HAS BEEN BORN
INTO AN UGLY HUMAN BODY.

341
00:16:43,654 --> 00:16:45,754
-I'M -- I'M NOT A CROW!

342
00:16:45,754 --> 00:16:48,154
I'M A -- A PERSON!

343
00:16:48,154 --> 00:16:52,820
I'M K-- RAE, REE, RU -- RUE.

344
00:16:52,820 --> 00:16:54,520
MY NAME IS RUE!

345
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:57,520
CAN I COME SEE YOU AGAIN?

346
00:16:57,520 --> 00:16:58,987
-YES.

347
00:16:58,987 --> 00:17:00,887
-GOODBYE!

348
00:17:00,887 --> 00:17:04,520
[ GEARS CLANKING ]

349
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,120
-WHAT'S GOING ON!?

350
00:17:06,120 --> 00:17:08,154
-THE STORY IS FLOWING BACKWARDS!
-WHAT!?

351
00:17:08,154 --> 00:17:09,620
-STOP IT! HURRY!

352
00:17:09,620 --> 00:17:13,020
STOP IT WITH YOUR PEN! FAKIR!

353
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:15,120
-[ Thinking ]
THE STORY'S DOUBLING BACK?

354
00:17:27,695 --> 00:17:30,195
[ GEARS CLANKING ]

355
00:17:30,195 --> 00:17:34,695
-I'VE EXPERIENCED
A LOT OF NEW FEELINGS

356
00:17:34,695 --> 00:17:37,028
SINCE BECOMING A HUMAN GIRL.

357
00:17:37,028 --> 00:17:39,095
IN THE BEGINNING,

358
00:17:39,095 --> 00:17:42,995
I DIDN'T THINK MY FEELINGS
FOR MYTHO WOULD GROW SO MUCH.

359
00:17:45,028 --> 00:17:48,195
-I WILL NEVER GO BACK --

360
00:17:48,195 --> 00:17:50,195
NOT TO THAT TIME
WHEN I CLUNG TO MY SWORD

361
00:17:50,195 --> 00:17:52,935
AND SAID NOTHING BUT WORDS THAT
DEPRIVED MYTHO OF HIS FREEDOM!

362
00:17:52,935 --> 00:17:55,935
-ALL OF MY FEELINGS
BELONG TO ME.

363
00:17:55,935 --> 00:17:59,935
ALL FEELINGS ARE PRECIOUS
TO WHOM THEY BELONG.

364
00:17:59,935 --> 00:18:02,268
AND I AM NOBODY'S MARIONETTE.

365
00:18:02,268 --> 00:18:04,668
-I WILL NO LONGER COWARD
BEFORE FATE!

366
00:18:04,668 --> 00:18:06,001
-WHATEVER IT TAKES!

367
00:18:06,001 --> 00:18:06,901
-WE'LL GUARD HIM!

368
00:18:06,901 --> 00:18:09,401
-TOGETHER!
-TOGETHER!

369
00:18:09,401 --> 00:18:12,901
[ UP-TEMPO CLASSICAL MUSIC
PLAYING ]

370
00:18:12,901 --> 00:18:16,001
-[ GASPS ]
JUST NOW, I HEARD HER VOICE!

371
00:18:17,301 --> 00:18:19,401
THAT'S RIGHT.

372
00:18:19,401 --> 00:18:22,768
SHE'S CHANGED ME.

373
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:26,001
I CAN WRITE!
I CAN WRITE A STORY ABOUT HER!

374
00:18:27,868 --> 00:18:32,268
B-BUT WAIT, THESE WORDS --
THEY'RE NOT MY WORDS.

375
00:18:32,268 --> 00:18:33,768
WHAT ARE THEY?

376
00:18:33,768 --> 00:18:35,801
[ GEARS CLANK ]
-OH!

377
00:18:35,801 --> 00:18:37,901
EVERYTHING STOP MOVING, ZURA!

378
00:18:37,901 --> 00:18:40,901
-THE STORY DOESN'T WANT
TO GO BACK ANY MORE THAN THAT.

379
00:18:40,901 --> 00:18:42,435
-WHO'S THAT, ZURA?

380
00:18:42,435 --> 00:18:45,201
UH, OH! ARE YOU A PUPPET, ZURA?

381
00:18:45,201 --> 00:18:47,301
-I AM A PUPPET.

382
00:18:47,301 --> 00:18:48,701
AND I AM YOU.

383
00:18:48,701 --> 00:18:51,208
YOU ARE ALSO ME.

384
00:18:51,208 --> 00:18:53,108
-I'M NOT UZURA, ZURA?

385
00:18:53,108 --> 00:18:56,675
-I AM A PUPPET
WHO COULD NOT HAVE A HEART.

386
00:18:56,675 --> 00:18:58,775
BUT YOU...

387
00:18:58,775 --> 00:19:00,108
-OOOH.

388
00:19:00,108 --> 00:19:01,341
[ DRIP! ]

389
00:19:01,341 --> 00:19:03,108
[ GASPS ]

390
00:19:03,108 --> 00:19:06,008
AHH.

391
00:19:06,008 --> 00:19:08,941
-NOW, GO BACK TO WHERE DUCK IS.

392
00:19:11,841 --> 00:19:12,841
-WAIT, ZURA!

393
00:19:12,841 --> 00:19:15,875
-THESE ARE...ALL HER FEELINGS.

394
00:19:15,875 --> 00:19:17,841
-I WANT TO GO BACK.

395
00:19:17,841 --> 00:19:21,108
I WANT TO GO BACK
AND HELP MYTHO!

396
00:19:21,108 --> 00:19:23,508
I WANT TO LEAVE THIS PLACE!

397
00:19:23,508 --> 00:19:25,741
-HER FEELINGS FOR MYTHO

398
00:19:25,741 --> 00:19:29,775
ARE SPILLING UP THROUGH MY HAND
AND OUT ONTO THE PAGE.

399
00:19:29,775 --> 00:19:31,275
"IN THAT TIME,

400
00:19:31,275 --> 00:19:34,041
"THE KNIGHT WHO HAD CAST AWAY
HIS SWORD CALLED HER NAME

401
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:37,275
IN ORDER TO LEAD HER
OUT OF THE DARKNESS!"

402
00:19:37,275 --> 00:19:41,075
DU-U-U-U-U-CK!

403
00:19:41,075 --> 00:19:43,508
DU-U-U-U-U-CK!
-[ GASPS ]

404
00:19:43,508 --> 00:19:44,775
FAKIR!

405
00:19:44,775 --> 00:19:48,275
FAKIR!

406
00:19:48,275 --> 00:19:50,748
-THERE. GO ON!

407
00:19:50,748 --> 00:19:52,081
-OH!

408
00:19:57,348 --> 00:19:58,648
WHOA!

409
00:20:00,115 --> 00:20:01,315
-[ GASPS ]

410
00:20:04,848 --> 00:20:06,581
DUCK!

411
00:20:06,581 --> 00:20:08,048
-FAKIR!

412
00:20:15,581 --> 00:20:20,081
DID YOU WRITE A STORY ABOUT ME,
THEN?

413
00:20:20,081 --> 00:20:22,215
-YEAH.

414
00:20:22,215 --> 00:20:24,481
-THANK YOU.

415
00:20:24,481 --> 00:20:26,481
-WHAT IS THIS?

416
00:20:26,481 --> 00:20:29,581
FOR HER TO LEAVE HERE
WITHOUT MY PERMISSION?

417
00:20:29,581 --> 00:20:31,515
SHE'S NOT TO BE UNDERESTIMATED.

418
00:20:31,515 --> 00:20:34,048
AND THANKS TO THIS,
THE STORY IS STILL STOPPED.

419
00:20:34,048 --> 00:20:35,215
[ GEARS CLANK ]
HM?

420
00:20:35,215 --> 00:20:36,781
OH.

421
00:20:36,781 --> 00:20:40,481
IT WOULD APPEAR THAT THERE IS
ONE WHO IS STILL DOUBLING BACK.

422
00:20:40,481 --> 00:20:44,781
YOU'RE GOING TO FIND OUT
SOMETHING YOU WISH YOU HADN'T.

423
00:20:44,781 --> 00:20:46,515
-NOW WHERE...AM I?

424
00:20:46,515 --> 00:20:47,815
-WHAT'S WRONG?

425
00:20:47,815 --> 00:20:49,481
-MY DAUGHTER'S BEEN KIDNAPPED
BY THE CROWS!

426
00:20:49,481 --> 00:20:51,555
-WHAT? WE'LL START
SEARCHING OVER THERE!

427
00:20:51,555 --> 00:20:52,888
-THANK YOU.

428
00:20:52,888 --> 00:20:55,188
-[ CRYING ]

429
00:20:55,188 --> 00:20:58,388
-THAT THERE -- THAT'S ME?

430
00:20:58,388 --> 00:20:59,955
THE MAN....

431
00:20:59,955 --> 00:21:03,988
AFTER ALL THIS,
I'M NOT THE RAVEN'S DAUGHTER?

432
00:21:03,988 --> 00:21:06,955
I HAD A MOTHER.
I HAD A FATHER.

433
00:21:06,955 --> 00:21:10,421
I'M A NORMAL HUMAN BEING?

434
00:21:10,421 --> 00:21:11,921
-[ CAWS ]

435
00:21:16,555 --> 00:21:18,588
-[ LAUGHS ]

436
00:21:18,588 --> 00:21:20,555
WHAT A WRETCHED FATE.

437
00:21:20,555 --> 00:21:22,155
-[ GASPS ]

438
00:21:24,855 --> 00:21:26,355
AAAAH!

439
00:21:26,355 --> 00:21:29,155
[ SCREAMING ]

440
00:21:29,155 --> 00:21:32,021
-HM?

441
00:21:32,021 --> 00:21:34,855
THE STORY'S
FINALLY STARTED MOVING.

442
00:21:34,855 --> 00:21:36,355
MY, MY.

443
00:21:36,355 --> 00:21:39,721
THANK GOODNESS, THANK GOODNESS.

444
00:21:41,921 --> 00:21:45,721
-OOH, SO THAT MEANS
I'M NOT UZURA, ZURA?

445
00:21:45,721 --> 00:21:49,955
MY HEART ISN'T LOVEY-DOVEY,
ZURA?

446
00:21:49,955 --> 00:21:51,961
UH, OH.

447
00:21:51,961 --> 00:21:53,495
WHERE AM I, ZURA?

448
00:21:53,495 --> 00:21:55,761
AHH.

449
00:21:55,761 --> 00:22:00,395
AAAH-AAAAAH.

450
00:22:02,961 --> 00:22:06,961
I'M UP HIGH, ZURA!

451
00:22:06,961 --> 00:22:09,661
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S "THOUGH
MY LOVE IS SMALL" PLAYS ]

452
00:22:21,195 --> 00:22:23,995
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

453
00:23:38,735 --> 00:23:41,201
-MY LOVE HAS DONE NOTHING
BUT MAKE YOU INTO THIS.

454
00:23:41,201 --> 00:23:42,968
I HAVE NO RIGHT TO LOVE YOU.

455
00:23:42,968 --> 00:23:44,968
-DUCK DOESN'T KNOW.

456
00:23:44,968 --> 00:23:46,601
THERE'S A THING
SHE DOESN'T KNOW.

457
00:23:46,601 --> 00:23:49,601
-JUST NOW,
I WAS AFRAID OF MYTHO.

458
00:23:49,601 --> 00:23:52,841
-EVEN IF I PUT WATER ON YOU,
YOU WON'T CHANGE BACK, ZURA?

459
00:23:52,841 --> 00:23:55,408
-THAT'S WHY I'M ASKING
FOR YOUR HELP, AUTOR.

460
00:23:55,408 --> 00:23:57,541
-SO THIS IS THE RAVEN.

461
00:23:57,541 --> 00:23:59,175
-THIS FRAIL, EARNEST LOVE --

462
00:23:59,175 --> 00:24:00,641
I MUST PROTECT THIS LOVE.

463
00:24:00,641 --> 00:24:05,341
-ALL YOU CHILDREN WHO LOVE
STORIES, COME GATHER 'ROUND.

464
00:24:05,341 --> 00:24:06,975
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

